energyml.witsml2_0.AbstractBottomHoleTem: One of either circulating or static temperature
energyml.witsml2_0.AbstractCementJob: Defines common elements for both cement job designs and reports.
energyml.witsml2_0.AbstractCementStage: Defines the information that is common to the cement job stage design and reports.
energyml.witsml2_0.AbstractIndexValue: Generic representation of pass, depth, or time values. Each derived element provides specialized implementation for specific content types or for optimization of the representation.
energyml.witsml2_0.AbstractIscwsaErrorCo: Describes the survey measurement or value that the error term applies to.
energyml.witsml2_0.AbstractItemWtOrVolPe: Item weight or volume per unit.
energyml.witsml2_0.AbstractLogDataContex: Defines a constraint against the data points in the log's channel. Each time the log is realized, only the data points satisfying this constraint are included.
energyml.witsml2_0.AbstractRotarySteerab: Choice placeholder in a rotary steerable tool.
energyml.witsml2_0.AbstractWellLocation: Location Schema. This is a location that is expressed in terms of 2D coordinates. So that the location can be understood, the coordinate reference system (CRS) must be known. The survey location is given by a pair of tagged values. The pairs may be: (1) latitude/longitude, (2) easting/northing, (3) westing/southing, (4) projectedX/projectedY, or (5) localX/localY. The appropriate pair must be chosen for the data.
energyml.witsml2_0.Assembly: Container element for assemblies, or a collection of all assembly information.
energyml.witsml2_0.Attachment: A dedicated object used to attach digital supplemental data (for example, a graphic or PDF file) to another data object. The attachment is captured as a base 64 binary type.
energyml.witsml2_0.AuthorizationStatus: Specifies the status of the current tool error model.
energyml.witsml2_0.Azi: Describes what survey measurement or value the error term applies to.
energyml.witsml2_0.AziRef: Reference to the azimuth of the trajectory
energyml.witsml2_0.BHPExtension: Information on bottom hole pressure during this event.
energyml.witsml2_0.BearingType: Specifies the bearing type of a motor.
energyml.witsml2_0.BeaufortScaleIntegerC: An estimated wind strength based on the Beaufort Wind Scale. Values range from 0 (calm) to 12 (hurricane).
energyml.witsml2_0.BendAngle: Used with point-the-bit type of rotary steerable system tools; describes the angle of the bit.
energyml.witsml2_0.BendOffset: Used with point-the-bit type of rotary steerable system tools; describes the angle of the bit.
energyml.witsml2_0.BhaRun: The object used to capture information about one run of the drill string into and out of the hole. The drill string configuration is described in the Tubular object. That is, one drill string configuration may be used for many runs.
energyml.witsml2_0.BhaStatus: Stage of the BHA (plan, progress, final)
energyml.witsml2_0.BitDullCode: Specifies the reason a drill bit was declared inoperable; these codes were originally defined by the IADC.
energyml.witsml2_0.BitReasonPulled: Specifies the reason for pulling a drill bit from the wellbore, these codes were originally defined by the IADC.
energyml.witsml2_0.BitRecord: Bit Record Component Schema. Captures information that describes the bit and problems with the bit. Many of the problems are classified using IADC codes that are specified as enumerated lists in WITSML.
energyml.witsml2_0.BitType: Specifies the  values that represent the type of drill or core bit.
energyml.witsml2_0.BladeShapeType: Blade shape of the stabilizer: melon, spiral, straight, etc.
energyml.witsml2_0.BladeType: Specifies the blade type of the stabilizer.
energyml.witsml2_0.BopType: Specifies the type of blowout preventer.
energyml.witsml2_0.BoreholeString: A section of a borehole. Used to define the drilled hole that corresponds to the wellbore. A collection of contiguous and non-overlapping borehole sections is allowed. Each section has depth range, diameter, and kind.
energyml.witsml2_0.BoreholeStringReferen: Reference to a borehole string identifier
energyml.witsml2_0.BoreholeStringSet: Borehole string container element, or a collection of all borehole strings.
energyml.witsml2_0.BoreholeType: Specifies the values for the type of borehole.
energyml.witsml2_0.BottomHoleCirculating: Circulating temperature at the bottom of the hole.
energyml.witsml2_0.BottomHoleStaticTempe: Static temperature at the bottom of the hole.
energyml.witsml2_0.BoxPinConfig: Specifies values that represent the type of box and pin configuration.
energyml.witsml2_0.CalibrationPointRole: The role of a calibration point in a log depth registration.
energyml.witsml2_0.CasingConnectionType: Container element for casing connections or collection of all casing connections information.
energyml.witsml2_0.CasingConnectionTypes: Specifies the values for connection type of casing.
energyml.witsml2_0.CementDesignStage: Configuration and other information about the cement stage.
energyml.witsml2_0.CementJob: Used to capture information about cementing operations, which are done to seal the annulus after a casing string has been run, to seal a lost circulation zone, or to set a plug to support directional drilling operations or seal a well so that it may be abandoned.
energyml.witsml2_0.CementJobDesign: Design and other information about the cement job
energyml.witsml2_0.CementJobEvaluation: A top-level object that is used to record the testing and evaluation of a previously performed cement job.
energyml.witsml2_0.CementJobReport: The as-built report of the job after it has been done.
energyml.witsml2_0.CementPumpScheduleSte: Cement Pump Schedule Component Schema, which defines the cement pumping schedule for a given step in a cement job.
energyml.witsml2_0.CementStageDesign: Configuration and other information about the cement stage.
energyml.witsml2_0.CementStageReport: Report of key parameters for a stage of cement job.
energyml.witsml2_0.Channel:
A channel object. It corresponds roughly to the LogCurveInfo structure in WITSML1411, and directly corresponds to the ChannelMetadataRecord structure in ETP. In historian terminology, a channel corresponds directly to a tag.
Channels are the fundamental unit of organization for WITSML logs.
energyml.witsml2_0.ChannelData: Contains the bulk data for the log, either as a base64-encoded string or as a reference to an external file.
energyml.witsml2_0.ChannelDerivation: Specifies  the source of data in a channel.
energyml.witsml2_0.ChannelIndex: A read-only class that is the union of those channel indexes that are shared by all channels in the channel set.
energyml.witsml2_0.ChannelIndexType: Specifies the type of index used by the channel.
energyml.witsml2_0.ChannelSet: A grouping of channels with a compatible index, for some purpose. Each channel has its own index. A â€˜compatibleâ€™ index simply means that all of the channels are either in time or in depth using a common datum.
energyml.witsml2_0.ChannelState: Specifies the source of the data values in the channel, e.g., calculated from another source, or from archive, or raw real-time, etc.
energyml.witsml2_0.ChannelStatus: Specifies the status of the channel (growing object): active, inactive, closed
energyml.witsml2_0.ChannelValueContext: Describes the data for the log in terms of  the value of a given channel.
energyml.witsml2_0.Chromatograph: Analysis done to determine the components in a show.
energyml.witsml2_0.Coating: Specifies the values for the type of inside or outside coating of this piece of equipment.
energyml.witsml2_0.CompletionStatus: Specifies the values of the status of a wellbore completion.
energyml.witsml2_0.CompletionStatusHisto: Information on the collection of Completion StatusHistory.
energyml.witsml2_0.ConcentrationParamete: Specifies the values for mud log parameters that are measured in units of concentration.
energyml.witsml2_0.Connection: Tubular Connection Component Schema. Describes dimensions and properties of a connection between tubulars.
energyml.witsml2_0.ConnectionFormType: Specifies the values for the type of equipment-to-equipment connection.
energyml.witsml2_0.ConnectionPosition: Specifies the position of a connection.
energyml.witsml2_0.ContactIntervalSet: Information on a collection of contact intervals. Contains one or more "xxxInterval" objects, each representing the details of a single physical connection between well and reservoir, e.g., the perforation details, depth, reservoir connected. Meaning: this is the physical nature of a connection from reservoir to wellbore.
energyml.witsml2_0.Cost: The price of an item, with a currency indication.
energyml.witsml2_0.CuttingsGeology: Container for Cuttings Lithology items. The mud logger at the wellsite takes regular samples of drilled cuttings while the well is being drilled and examines the cuttings to determine the rock types (lithologies) present in each sample. The cuttings samples will typically contain a mix of different lithologies in each sample because there may have been multiple rock types that were drilled within the sample depth interval and there can also be mixing of cuttings as they travel up the wellbore and are collected on the shakers. CuttingsGeology therefore will typically contain multiple lithology elements for each interval so that the percentages of each lithology in the sample along with the more detailed geological description can be recorded.
energyml.witsml2_0.CuttingsGeologyInterv: A depth range along the wellbore containing one or more lithology types and information about how the cuttings were sampled.
energyml.witsml2_0.CuttingsIntervalLitho: The description of a single rock type in this interval. Can include one or more CuttingsIntervalShow objects for hydrocarbon show evaluation of the individual lithology.
energyml.witsml2_0.CuttingsIntervalShow: A set of measurements or observations on cuttings samples describing the evaluation of a hydrocarbon show based on observation of hydrocarbon staining and fluorescence. For information on procedures for show evaluation, see the WITSML Technical Usage Guide.
energyml.witsml2_0.DayCost: Day Cost SchemaSchema. Captures daily cost information for the object (cost item) to which it is attached.
energyml.witsml2_0.DeflectionMethod: Specifies the method used to direct the deviation of the trajectory in directional drilling.
energyml.witsml2_0.Depth: Describes what survey measurement or value the error term applies to.
energyml.witsml2_0.DepthRegCalibrationPo: A mapping of pixel positions on the log image to rectified or depth-registered positions on the log image. Specifically, pixels along the depth track are tagged with the matching measured depth for that position.
energyml.witsml2_0.DepthRegImage: Information about the composition, layout, and depth registration of a digital image of a well log, typically a scanned image of a paper well log document.
energyml.witsml2_0.DepthRegLogRect: A region of an image containing a log rectangle.
energyml.witsml2_0.DepthRegLogSection: Defines the description and coordinates of a well log section, the curves on the log. An important XSDelement to note is log:refNameString; it is a reference to the actual log/data (in a WITSML server) that this raster image represents; this object does not contain the log data.
energyml.witsml2_0.DepthRegParameter: Specifies parameters associated with the log section and includes top and bottom indexes, a description string, and mnemonic.
energyml.witsml2_0.DepthRegPoint: The position of a pixel of an image, in x-y coordinates.
energyml.witsml2_0.DepthRegRectangle: Uses 4 corner points (Ul, Ur, Ll, Lr) to define the position (pixel) of a rectangular area of an image, using x-y coordinates. Most objects point to this object because most are rectangles, and use this schema to define each rectangle.
energyml.witsml2_0.DepthRegTrack: Horizontal track layout of the rectified log image that identifies the rectangle for a single log track.
energyml.witsml2_0.DepthRegTrackCurve: Descriptions of the actual curve, including elements such as line weight, color, and style, within a log track.
energyml.witsml2_0.DerrickType: Specifies the type of drilling derrick.
energyml.witsml2_0.DistanceEastWest: The distance to a one-minute boundary on the east or west of a point. USA Public Land Survey System.
energyml.witsml2_0.DistanceNorthSouth: The distance to a one-minute boundary on the north or south of a point. USA Public Land Survey System
energyml.witsml2_0.DownholeComponentRefe: Reference to a downhole component identifier
energyml.witsml2_0.DownholeExtension: Information on downhole related to this event.
energyml.witsml2_0.DownholeString: A section of the downhole component equipment.  Strings in the completion including casing, tubing, and rod strings .A completion may have multiple sets of strings, which may be nested each inside another, or run in parallel as in dual string completions; all strings are contained in a parent wellbore. Each string is composed of equipment, and may also contain accessories and/or assemblies.
energyml.witsml2_0.DownholeStringReferen: Refernce to a downhole string identifier
energyml.witsml2_0.DownholeStringSet: Information on a collection of downhole strings
energyml.witsml2_0.DownholeStringType: Specifies the values for the type of downhole strings.
energyml.witsml2_0.DrawWorksType: Specifies the type of draw works.
energyml.witsml2_0.DrillActivityClassTyp: Activity classifier, e.g., planned, unplanned, downtime
energyml.witsml2_0.DrillActivityCode: A code to specify the drilling activity.
energyml.witsml2_0.DrillReport: Used to capture a daily drilling report focused on reporting from the operator to partners or to a governmental agency. For a similar report whose focus is service company to operator, see the OpsReport object.
energyml.witsml2_0.DrillReportControlInc: Information about a well control incident that occurred during the drill report period.
energyml.witsml2_0.DrillReportCoreInfo: General information about a core taken during the drill report period.
energyml.witsml2_0.DrillReportEquipFailu: General information about equipment failure that occurred during the drill report period.
energyml.witsml2_0.DrillReportFormTestIn: General information about a wireline formation test that occurred during the drill report period.
energyml.witsml2_0.DrillReportGasReading: General information about a gas reading taken during the drill report period.
energyml.witsml2_0.DrillReportLithShowIn: General information about the lithology and shows in an interval encountered during the drill report period.
energyml.witsml2_0.DrillReportLogInfo: General information about a log conducted during the drill report period.
energyml.witsml2_0.DrillReportPerfInfo: General information about a perforation interval related to the drill report period.
energyml.witsml2_0.DrillReportPorePressu: General information about pore pressure related to the drill report period.
energyml.witsml2_0.DrillReportStatusInfo: General status information for the drill report period.
energyml.witsml2_0.DrillReportStratInfo: General information about stratigraphy for the drill report period.
energyml.witsml2_0.DrillReportSurveyStat: Trajectory station information for the drill report period.
energyml.witsml2_0.DrillReportWellTestIn: General information about a production well test conducted during the drill report period.
energyml.witsml2_0.DrillReportWellboreIn: General information about a wellbore for a drill report period.
energyml.witsml2_0.DrillingParameters: Information regarding drilling: ROP, WOB, torque, etc.
energyml.witsml2_0.DrillingParams: The bottomhole assembly drilling parameters schema, which contains statistical and calculated operations data for the run, related to depths, activities, temperature, pressure, flow rates, torque, etc.
energyml.witsml2_0.DriveType: Specifies the type of work-string drive (rotary system).
energyml.witsml2_0.EcdStatistics: Information on equivalent circulating density statistics.
energyml.witsml2_0.ElevCodeEnum: Specifies values for the type of local or permanent reference datum for vertical gravity-based (i.e., elevation and vertical depth) and measured depth coordinates within the context of a well. This list includes local points (e.g., kelly bushing) used as a datum and vertical reference datums (e.g., mean sea level).
energyml.witsml2_0.Equipment: Information on a piece of equipment. Each kind of equipment in the set has a type (what it is) and attributes common across all instances of that type of equipment. The String Equipment then references these common attributes.
energyml.witsml2_0.EquipmentConnection: Information detailing the connection between two components.
energyml.witsml2_0.EquipmentSet: Information on the collection of equipment.
energyml.witsml2_0.EquipmentType: Specifies the values for type of equipment.
energyml.witsml2_0.EquipmentTypeExt: An extension of possible equipment types.
energyml.witsml2_0.ErrorPropagationMode: Specifies the codes for the various propagation modes.
energyml.witsml2_0.ErrorTermSource: Specifies the codes for the various classes of error sources.
energyml.witsml2_0.EtpDataType: Specifies the type of data contained in a channel to facilitate data transfer using the Energistics Transfer Protocol (ETP).
energyml.witsml2_0.EventClassType: Qualifies the type of event: daily report, job, npt, etc.
energyml.witsml2_0.EventType: The type of the referencing event
energyml.witsml2_0.ExtPropNameValue: Name-value extensions for the equipment property.
energyml.witsml2_0.FileNameType: Specifies the type of file referenced.
energyml.witsml2_0.FluidLocation: Location of fluid in the wellbore.
energyml.witsml2_0.FluidsReport: Used to capture an analysis of the drilling mud.
energyml.witsml2_0.ForceParameterKind: Specifies the values for mud log parameters that are measured in units of force.
energyml.witsml2_0.GasInMud: Information on amount of gas in the mud.
energyml.witsml2_0.GeochronologicalUnit: A unit of geological time that can be used as part of an interpretation of a geology sequence. Use it for major units of geological time such as "Paleozoic", "Mesozoic" or for more detailed time intervals such as "Permian", "Triassic", "Jurassic", etc.
energyml.witsml2_0.GeodeticWellLocation: Location of the well by latitude and longitude.
energyml.witsml2_0.GeologyFeature: Geology features found in the location of the borehole string.
energyml.witsml2_0.GeologyType: Specifies the values for type of geology.
energyml.witsml2_0.GradeType: Specifies the values for the grade level of this piece of equipment.
energyml.witsml2_0.GravelPackInterval: The location/interval of the gravel pack, including its history.
energyml.witsml2_0.HoleCasingType: Specifies values for the types of hole casing.
energyml.witsml2_0.HoleOpener: Hole Opener Component Schema. Describes the hole-opener tool (often called a â€˜reamerâ€™) used on the tubular string.
energyml.witsml2_0.HoleOpenerType: Specifies the types of hole openers.
energyml.witsml2_0.Hse: Operations Health, Safety and Environment Schema. Captures data related to HSE events (e.g., tests, inspections, meetings, and drills), test values (e.g., pressure tested to), and/or incidents (e.g., discharges, non-compliance notices received, etc.).
energyml.witsml2_0.Hydrocyclone: Rig Hydrocyclones Schema. A hydrocyclone is a cone-shaped device for separating fluids and the solids dispersed in fluids.
energyml.witsml2_0.ISO13503_2SieveAnalys: Proppant properties on percent retained and sieve number. Data from this ISO anaylsis.
energyml.witsml2_0.IadcBearingWearCode: Specifies the condition codes for the bearing wear.
energyml.witsml2_0.IadcIntegerCode: Specifies the IADC integer codes for the inner or outer tooth rows.
energyml.witsml2_0.Inc: Describes what survey measurement or value the error term applies to.
energyml.witsml2_0.Incident: Operations HSE Schema. Captures data for a specific incident.
energyml.witsml2_0.IndexDirection: Specifies the direction of the index, whether decreasing or increasing.
energyml.witsml2_0.IndexRangeContext: Describes the data context for a log in terms of a starting and ending index. When this context is used, each realization of the log includes all data points from the log's channel set that follow between the specified start and end index.
energyml.witsml2_0.InterpretedGeology:
A container object for zero or more InterpretedGeologyInterval objects. The container references a specific wellbore, a depth interval, a growing object status, and a collection of interpreted geology intervals.
These values are manually entered per sample by the wellsite geologist or mud logger as an interpretation of the actual lithology sequence along the length of the wellbore by correlating the percentage lithologies observed in the cuttings samples along with other data (typically the drill rate and gamma ray curves), to estimate the location of the boundaries between the different lithology types. This analysis creates a sequence of individual lithologies along the wellbore. Therefore, InterpretedGeology typically contains a single lithology element for each interval that captures the detailed geological description of the lithology.
energyml.witsml2_0.InterpretedGeologyInt:
Represents a depth interval along the wellbore which contains a single interpreted lithology type. It can be used to:

	- carry information about geochronology and lithostratigraphy
	- create a pre-well geological prognosis with chronostratigraphic, lithostratigraphic, and lithology entries.
energyml.witsml2_0.InterpretedIntervalLi: The description of a single rock type that is used within InterpretedGeologyInterval. There can only be one of these in each InterpretedGeologyInterval.
energyml.witsml2_0.IntervalStatusHistory: Information on the status history in the interval.
energyml.witsml2_0.IscwsaAuthorizationDa: Authorization state of some entity. The main goal of the Industry Steering Committee on Wellbore Survey Accuracy (ISCWSA) is to to produce and maintain standards for the industry relating to wellbore survey accuracy.
energyml.witsml2_0.IscwsaErrorCoefficien: Describes what survey measurement or value the error term applies to.
energyml.witsml2_0.IscwsaErrorTerm: Captures the reference error terms that are included in error models using ErrorTermValues.
energyml.witsml2_0.IscwsaErrorTermValue: The instantiation of an error term in an error model.The content of this element (a number) is the variance scaling factor of the term in the model.
energyml.witsml2_0.IscwsaModelParameters: Various parameters controlling the generation of the survey variance.
energyml.witsml2_0.IscwsaNameAndDescript:
A generic type which captures a name and a description of something.
The semantics of the something is defined by the parent element.
energyml.witsml2_0.IscwsaNomenclature: A nomenclature for the description of error terms.
energyml.witsml2_0.IscwsaSurveyToolOpera: Describes the survey acquisition context in which an error model is valid as a sequence of constraints.

Inclination interval for a particular operating mode.
Intervals may overlap to suppress mode flip-flopping, but should cover
the entire valid range of the tool.
energyml.witsml2_0.ItemState: These values represent the state of a WITSML object.
energyml.witsml2_0.Jar: WITSML - Tubular Jar Component Schema. Captures information about jars, which are mechanical or hydraulic devices used in the drill stem to deliver an impact load to another component of the drill stem, especially when that component is stuck.
energyml.witsml2_0.JarAction: Specifies the type of jar action.
energyml.witsml2_0.LineStyle: Specifies the style of line used to define the DepthRegTrackCurve.
energyml.witsml2_0.LithologyQualifier: A description of minerals or accessories that constitute a fractional part of a CuttingsIntervalLithology.
energyml.witsml2_0.LithostratigraphicUni:
The name of a lithostratigraphy, with the "kind" attribute specifying the lithostratigraphic unit-hierarchy (group, formation, member or bed). The entry at each level is free text for the local lithostratigraphy at that level in the hierarchy. If a single hierarchy is defined, it is assumed this is at the formation level in the hierarchy and kind=formation should be used for the entry.
Used to hold information about the stratigraphic units that an interpreted lithology may belong to. These are based primarily on the differences between rock types rather than their specific age. For example, in the Grand Canyon, some of the major lithostratigraphic units are the "Navajo", "Kayenta", "Wingate", "Chinle" and "Moenkopi" formations, each of which is represented by a particular set of rock properties or characteristics.
energyml.witsml2_0.Log: Primarily a container for one or more channel sets (ChannelSet). In WITSML v2.+, most of the log information is now at the channel set level. The concept of multiple channel sets in a single log is significant change from WITSML v1.4.1.1, where each log represented exactly one group of curves and their data. For more information about log organization and how it works, see the WITSML Technical Usage Guide.
energyml.witsml2_0.LogChannelAxis: Metadata by which the array structure of a compound value is defined. It defines one axis of an array type used in a log channel.
energyml.witsml2_0.LogIndexType: These values represent the type of data used as an index value for a log.
energyml.witsml2_0.LogRectangleType: Specifies the type of content from the original log defined by the rectangle.
energyml.witsml2_0.LogSectionType: Specifies the type of log section.
energyml.witsml2_0.LoggingMethod: Specifies the method of logging used to record or produce the data in the log.
energyml.witsml2_0.MaterialType: Specifies the primary type of material that a component is made of.
energyml.witsml2_0.MeasureOrQuantity: A measure with a UOM or a quantity (without a UOM). This should not be used except in situations where the underlying class of data is captured elsewhere, e.g., in a measure class.
energyml.witsml2_0.MeasuredDepthCoord: A measured depth coordinate in a wellbore. Positive moving from the reference datum toward the bottomhole. All coordinates with the same datum (and same UOM) can be considered to be in the same coordinate reference system (CRS) and are thus directly comparable.
energyml.witsml2_0.MeasurementType: Specifies the type of sensor in a tubular string. The source (except for "CH density porosity", "CH neutron porosity", "OH density porosity" and "OH neutron porosity") of the values and the descriptions is the POSC V2.2 "well log trace class" standard instance values, which are documented as "A classification of well log traces based on specification of a range of characteristics. Traces may be classed according to the type of physical characteristic they are meant to measure."
energyml.witsml2_0.MemberObject: Defines a member of an objectGroup.
energyml.witsml2_0.Motor: Tubular Motor Component Schema. Used to capture properties about a motor used in a tubular string.
energyml.witsml2_0.MudClass: Specifies the class of a drilling fluid.
energyml.witsml2_0.MudDensityStatistics: Mud density readings at average or channel.
energyml.witsml2_0.MudGas: Information on gas in the mud and gas peak.
energyml.witsml2_0.MudLogParameter: Information around the mud log: type, time taken, top and bottom depth, pressure gradient, etc.
energyml.witsml2_0.MudLogPressureGradien: Describes the kind and value of mud log parameters that are expressed in units of pressure gradient.
energyml.witsml2_0.MudLogPressureParamet: Describes the kind and value of mud log parameters that are expressed in units of pressure.
energyml.witsml2_0.MudLogReport: Details of wellbore geology intervals, drilling parameters, chromatograph, mud gas, etc., data within an MD interval.
energyml.witsml2_0.MudLogStringParameter: Stores the values of parameters that are described by character strings.
Specifies values for mud log parameters that are described by character strings.
energyml.witsml2_0.MudLosses: Operations Mud Losses Schema.Captures volumes of mud lost for specific activities or onsite locations and total volumes for surface and down hole.
energyml.witsml2_0.MudSubClass: The name of a data extension.
energyml.witsml2_0.MudlogReportInterval: The interval at which the report on the mud log was taken, detailing cuttings, interpreted geology, and show evaluation.
energyml.witsml2_0.MwdTool: Tubular MWD Tool Component Schema. Used to capture operating parameters of the MWD tool.
energyml.witsml2_0.NameTagLocation: Specifies the values for the locations where an equipment tag might be found.
energyml.witsml2_0.NameTagNumberingSchem: Specifies the values of the specifications for creating equipment tags.
energyml.witsml2_0.NameTagTechnology: Specifies the values for the mechanisms for attaching an equipment tag to an item.
energyml.witsml2_0.NonNegativeFraction: A floating point value between zero (inclusive) and one (inclusive).
energyml.witsml2_0.NorthOrSouth: Specifies the north or south direction.
energyml.witsml2_0.ObjectContext: Specifies the range of index values for a log by reference to another object (or sub-object) which contains the index range as part of its data.
energyml.witsml2_0.ObjectSequence: Defines a sequence number with an optional description attribute.
energyml.witsml2_0.OpenHoleInterval: The location/interval of the open hole and its history.
energyml.witsml2_0.OpsReport: Used to capture a daily drilling report focused on reporting from the service company to the operator. For a similar object whose focus is operator to partner or to governmental agency, see DrillReport. This object is uniquely identified within the context of one wellbore object.
energyml.witsml2_0.OpsReportVersion: Version of the report, e.g., preliminary, normal, final, etc.
energyml.witsml2_0.OtherConnectionType: Allows you to enter a connection type other than the ones in the standard list.
energyml.witsml2_0.OtherConnectionTypes: Specifies the values for other types of connections.
energyml.witsml2_0.PIDXCommodityCode: UNSPSC (Segment 71) commodity code from oil and gas extraction and production enhancement services family. For more information, see http://www.pidx.org/.
energyml.witsml2_0.PassIndexedDepth: Qualifies depth based on pass, direction and depth
energyml.witsml2_0.PerfConveyanceMethod: Information on how perforation is conveyed: slick line, wireline, tubing
energyml.witsml2_0.PerfSlot: Information on slot resulting from a perforation.
energyml.witsml2_0.PerforationSet: Information regarding a collection of perforations.
energyml.witsml2_0.PerforationSetInterva: The location/interval of the perforation set and its history.
energyml.witsml2_0.PerforationSets: Information on the collection of perforation sets.
energyml.witsml2_0.PerforationStatus: Specifies the set of values for the status of a perforation.
energyml.witsml2_0.PerforationStatusHist: Information on the collection of perforation status history.
energyml.witsml2_0.PerforationToolType: Species the values for the type of perforation tool used to create the perfs.
energyml.witsml2_0.Personnel: Operations Personnel Component Schema. List each company on the rig at the time of the report and key information about each company, for example, name, type of service, and number of personnel.
energyml.witsml2_0.PhysicalStatus: Specifies the values for the physical status of an interval.
energyml.witsml2_0.PointMetadata:
Used to declare that data points in a specific WITSML log channel may contain value attributes (e.g., quality identifiers). This declaration is independent from the possibility that ETP may have sent ValueAttributes in real time.
If an instance of PointMetadata is present for a Channel, then the value for that point is represented as an array in the bulk data string.
energyml.witsml2_0.PresTestType: Specifies the types of pressure test(s) conducted during a drilling report period.
energyml.witsml2_0.PressureGradientParam: Specifies values for mud log parameters that are measured in units of pressure gradient.
energyml.witsml2_0.PressureParameterKind: Specifies values for mud log parameters that are measured in units of pressure.
energyml.witsml2_0.PrincipalMeridian: Specifies values for the principal meridians for the United States Public Land Surveys.
energyml.witsml2_0.ProppantAgentKind: Specifies the type of proppant agent: ceramic, resin, sand, etc.
energyml.witsml2_0.PublicLandSurveySyste: Land survey system that describes the well by range, township, section, etc.
Some combination of NE, NW, SW, SE, N2, S2, E2, W2, C, TRxx, LTnn. USA Public Land Survey System.
Designates a particular quarter of a township. USA Public Land Survey System.
energyml.witsml2_0.PumpActionIntegerCode: Pump Action: 1 = single acting, 2 = double acting.
energyml.witsml2_0.PumpOpType: Specifies type of well operation being conducted while this pump was in use.
energyml.witsml2_0.ReadingKind: Specifies if the reading was measured or estimated.
energyml.witsml2_0.RefWellbore: Data that represents a foreign key to a wellbore. The wellbore may be defined within the context of another well.
energyml.witsml2_0.RefWellboreRig: A reference to a rig within a wellbore. The wellbore may be defined within the context of another well. This value represents a foreign key from one node to another.
energyml.witsml2_0.RefWellboreTrajectory: A reference to a trajectoryStation in a wellbore. The trajectoryStation may be defined within the context of another wellbore. This value represents a foreign key from one element to another.
energyml.witsml2_0.ReferenceContainer: Information on containing or contained components.
energyml.witsml2_0.Rheometer: Rheometer readings taken during a drill report period. A rheometer is viscosimeter use for some fluid measurements, particularly when solid suspension properties are needed.
energyml.witsml2_0.Rig: Rig Schema. Used to capture information unique to a drilling rig. For information about the usage of a rig in a specific operation, see the RigUtilization object.
energyml.witsml2_0.RigType: Specifies the type of drilling rig.
energyml.witsml2_0.RigUtilization: Rig Utilization Schema. Used to capture information related to the usage of a specific rig. For information unique to the rig itself, see the Rig object.
energyml.witsml2_0.Risk: Risk Schema. Used to provide a central location for capturing risk information about the well design and other well-related data objects.
energyml.witsml2_0.RiskSubCategory: Specifies the sub-category of risk, in relation to value of Risk Category.
energyml.witsml2_0.RodConnectionType: A type of rod connection, e.g., latched, threaded, welded, etc.
energyml.witsml2_0.RodConnectionTypes: Specifies the values for the connection type of rod.
energyml.witsml2_0.RopStatistics: Measurements on minimum, average and maximum rates of penetration (ROP) and the channel from which this data was calculated.
energyml.witsml2_0.RotarySteerableTool: Rotary Steerable Tool Component Schema. Captures size and performance information about the rotary steerable tool used in the tubular string.
energyml.witsml2_0.RpmStatistics: Measurement of the average turn rate and the channel from which the data was calculated.
energyml.witsml2_0.ScaleType: Specifies the main line scale types.
energyml.witsml2_0.Scr: Operations Slow Circulation Rates (SCR) Component Schema.
energyml.witsml2_0.ScrType: Specifies the type of slow circulation rate.
energyml.witsml2_0.SectionNumber: Sections are numbered "1" through "36." Irregular sections may be designated with a single value after a decimal point. USA Public Land Survey System.
energyml.witsml2_0.ShowEvaluation:
A container object for zero or more ShowEvaluationInterval objects. The container references a specific wellbore, a depth interval, a growing object status, and a collection of show evaluation intervals.
In a similar way to the InterpretedGeology, these are manually entered by the wellsite geologist or mud logger as an interpretation of the hydrocarbon show along the wellbore, based on the raw readings from one or more show analyses of individual show tests on cuttings samples.
energyml.witsml2_0.ShowEvaluationInterva: An interpretation of the overall hydrocarbon show derived from analysis of individual show tests on cuttings samples. An interval in the wellbore for which data is manually entered by the wellsite geologist or mud logger as an interpretation of the hydrocarbon show along the wellbore, based on the raw readings from one or more show analyses of individual show tests on cuttings samples.
energyml.witsml2_0.ShowFluid: Specifies the type of fluid analyzed in this interval.
energyml.witsml2_0.ShowFluorescence: Specifies the intensity and color of the show.
energyml.witsml2_0.ShowLevel: Specifies another qualifier for the show: blooming or streaming.
energyml.witsml2_0.ShowRating: Specifies the quality of the fluid showing at this interval.
energyml.witsml2_0.ShowSpeed: Specifies an indication of both the solubility of the oil and the permeability of the show. The speed can vary from instantaneous to very slow.
energyml.witsml2_0.SlotsInterval: The location/interval of the slots and the history.
energyml.witsml2_0.Stabilizer: Tubular Stablizer Component Schema. Captures dimension and operation information about stabilizers used in the tubular string.
energyml.witsml2_0.StateDetailActivity: Specifies the state of a drilling activity (DrillActivity).
energyml.witsml2_0.StimAdditive: Provides generic attributes associated with defining an additive used for stimulation.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimAdditiveKind: Specifies the type of stimulation additive added to the fluid used in the stim job.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimEvent: Provides a mechanism to capture general events that occurred during a stage of a stimulation job.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimFetTest: A diagnostic test that determines fluid efficiency. Fluid efficiency test (FET).
energyml.witsml2_0.StimFetTestAnalysisMe: Specifies the types of stimulation FET analysis methods.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimFlowPath: The fluid flow path for used when pumping a stage in a stimulation job.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimFlowPathType: Specifies the type of flow paths used in a stimulation job.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimFluid: The characteristics and recipe of the stimulation fluid without proppant.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimFluidSubtype: Specifies the secondary qualifier for fluid type, e.g., acid, base, condensate, etc.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimISO13503_5Point: A stress, conductivity, permeability, and temperature data point.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimJob: Parent object (transferrable object) for all the information about one stimulation job. A stimulation job has multiple stages, and each stage has multiple steps.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimJobDiversion: Captures the high-level description of the diversion method used in the stimulation job.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimJobDiversionMetho: Specifies the type of diversion used during a stimulation job.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimJobLogCatalog: A group of logs from a stimulation job, one log per stage.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimJobMaterialCatalo: A listing of materials for a particular job. Any stage of the stim job can reference material(s) in the catalog, which eliminates the need to repeat the materials for each stage.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimJobStage: Stage treated during a stimulation job.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimJobStep: A step in the treatment of a stage for a stimulation job.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimMaterial: Materials as a concept refers to the materials left in the well or consumed in the process of making the stimulation; it does not refer the carrier fluid.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimMaterialKind: Specifies the type of stimulation material.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimPerforationCluste: Information about a set of perforations.  The assumption is that all perforations within a given set are created with the same device or method.

Provides mechanism for combining perforation clusters into a group. This could be used to specify the set of existing perforations present in a well before starting a stimulation job, for example, for a re-frac job.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimPressureFlowRate: In an injection step test, the injection rate at a particular pressure.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimProppantAgent: Captures a description of a proppant used in a stimulation job.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimPumpFlowBackTest: Diagnostic test involving flowing a well back after treatment.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimPumpFlowBackTestS: In a step-down pump diagnostics test, this object contains all the data for a particular step in that test.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimShutInPressure: A pressure measurement taken at a certain time after the well has been shut in.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimStepDownTest: Diagnostic test involving flowing a well back after treatment.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimStepTest: An injection test, plotted pressure against injection rate, where a curve deflection and change of slope indicates the fracture breakdown pressure.
energyml.witsml2_0.StimTubular: In a production enhancement job, this item constitutes the data for a tubular in the hole.
energyml.witsml2_0.StnTrajCorUsed: Captures information about corrections applied to a trajectory station.
energyml.witsml2_0.StnTrajMatrixCov: Captures validation information for a covariance matrix.
energyml.witsml2_0.StnTrajRawData: Captures raw data for a trajectory station.
energyml.witsml2_0.StnTrajValid: Captures validation information for a survey.
energyml.witsml2_0.StringAccessory: StringAccessories contain the stringequipment's decorative components. An accessory is the stringEquipment or Stringsâ€™ decorative component.  An accessory is NOT directly screwed to the string. This part DOES NOT carry the weight of the rest of the String as opposed to the stringEquipment, which does. An Accessory is UNLIKE an Assembly on which the stringEquipment is built out of.
energyml.witsml2_0.StringEquipment: Information regarding equipment that composes (makes up) a string.
energyml.witsml2_0.StringEquipmentSet: Information on collection of set of equipment included in the string.
energyml.witsml2_0.SubStringType: Specifies the values  to further qualify a string type.
energyml.witsml2_0.SupportCraftType: Specifies the type of support craft.
energyml.witsml2_0.SurfEquipType: Specifies the type of surface equipment.
energyml.witsml2_0.SurveyProgram: Captures information about the nature, range, and sequence of directional surveying tools run in a wellbore for the management of positional uncertainty. This object is uniquely identified within the context of one wellbore object.
energyml.witsml2_0.SurveyToolOperatingMo: Specifies the codes for the ISCWSA survey tool operating modes.
energyml.witsml2_0.TimeIndexValue: Qualifies an index based on time.
energyml.witsml2_0.ToolErrorModel: Used to define a surveying tool error model. This object is globally unique.
energyml.witsml2_0.ToolErrorTermSet: Captures a set of surveying tool error terms which may be used in a toolErrorModel. This object is globally unique.
energyml.witsml2_0.TorqueCurrentStatisti: Measurement of the  average electric current and the channel from which the data was calculated.
energyml.witsml2_0.TorqueStatistics: Measurement of average torque and the channel from which the data was calculated.
energyml.witsml2_0.TrajStationStatus: Specifies the status of a trajectory station.
energyml.witsml2_0.TrajStationType: Specifies the type of directional survey station.
energyml.witsml2_0.TrajStnCalcAlgorithm: Specifies the trajectory station calculation algorithm.
energyml.witsml2_0.Trajectory: The trajectory object is used to capture information about a directional survey in a wellbore. It contains many trajectory stations to capture the information about individual survey points. This object is uniquely identified within the context of one wellbore object.
energyml.witsml2_0.TubingConnectionType: Container element for tubing connection types  or collection of tubing connection types.
energyml.witsml2_0.TubingConnectionTypes: Specifies the values for the connection types of tubing.
energyml.witsml2_0.Tubular: Used to capture information about the configuration of a drill string. For information about a use of this configuration, See the BhaRun object . This object is uniquely identified within the context of one wellbore object.
energyml.witsml2_0.TubularAssembly: Specifies the type (or purpose) of the tubular assembly.
energyml.witsml2_0.TubularComponent: Tubular Component Schema. Captures the order of the components in the XML instance,which is significant. The components are listed in the order in which they enter the hole. That is, the first component is the bit.
energyml.witsml2_0.TubularComponentType: Specifies the types of components that can be used in a tubular string. These are used to specify the type of component and multiple components are used to define a tubular string (Tubular).
energyml.witsml2_0.Tvd: Describes what survey measurement or value the error term applies to.
energyml.witsml2_0.TypeSurveyTool: Specifies values for the type of directional survey tool; a very generic classification.
energyml.witsml2_0.Well: Used to capture the general information about a well. Sometimes  called a "well header". Contains all information that is the same for all wellbores (sidetracks).
energyml.witsml2_0.WellCMLedger: Information regarding details of Jobs & Events
energyml.witsml2_0.WellCompletion: Information regarding  a wellhead stream with one or more wellbore completions (completed zones) in the well.
energyml.witsml2_0.WellControlIncidentTy: Specifies the type of a well control incident.
energyml.witsml2_0.WellDatum:
Defines the vertical datums associated with elevation, vertical depth 
and measured depth coordinates within the context of a well.
energyml.witsml2_0.WellDirection: Specifies values for the direction of flow of the fluids in a well facility (generally, injected or produced, or some combination).
energyml.witsml2_0.WellElevationCoord: A vertical (gravity-based) elevation coordinate within the context of a well. Positive moving upward from the reference datum.  All coordinates with the same datum (and same UOM) can be considered to be in the same coordinate reference system (CRS) and are thus directly comparable.
energyml.witsml2_0.WellFluid: Specifies values for the type of fluid being produced from or injected into a well facility.
energyml.witsml2_0.WellKillingProcedureT: Specifies the type of procedure used to stop (kill) the flow of formation fluids into a well. A well-killing procedure may be planned or unplanned. The particular situation determines what type of procedure is used.
energyml.witsml2_0.WellPurpose: Specifies values that represent the classification of a well or wellbore by the purpose for which it was initially drilled.
energyml.witsml2_0.WellTestType: Specifies the type of well test conducted.
energyml.witsml2_0.WellVerticalDepthCoor: A vertical (gravity-based) depth coordinate within the context of a well. Positive moving downward from the reference datum. All coordinates with the same datum (and same UOM) can be considered to be in the same coordinate reference system (CRS) and are thus directly comparable.
energyml.witsml2_0.Wellbore: Used to capture the general information about a wellbore. This information is sometimes called a "wellbore header". A wellbore represents the path from surface to a unique bottomhole location. The wellbore object is uniquely identified within the context of one well object.
energyml.witsml2_0.WellboreCompletion: The transferrable class of the WellboreCompletion object. Each individual wellbore completion data object represents a completion (i.e., open to flow) interval along a wellbore. Meaning "this section of wellbore is open to flow".
energyml.witsml2_0.WellboreFluidLocation: Specified the location where cement job fluid can be found.
energyml.witsml2_0.WellboreGeology: The transferrable class of the WellboreGeology object.
energyml.witsml2_0.WellboreGeometry: Used to capture information about the configuration of the permanently installed components in a wellbore. This object is uniquely identified within the context of one wellbore object.
energyml.witsml2_0.WellboreGeometrySecti: Wellbore Geometry Component Schema. Defines the "fixed" components in a wellbore. It does not define the "transient" drilling strings or the "hanging" production components.
energyml.witsml2_0.WellboreMarker: Used to capture information about a geologic formation that was encountered in a wellbore. This object is uniquely identified within the context of one wellbore object.
energyml.witsml2_0.WellboreShape: Specifies values to represent the classification of a wellbore based on its shape. The source of the values and the descriptions is the POSC V2.2 "facility class" standard instance values in classification system "POSC wellbore trajectory shape".
energyml.witsml2_0.WellboreType: Specifies the values for the classification of a wellbore with respect to its parent well/wellbore.
energyml.witsml2_0.WobStatistics: Measurement of average weight on bit and channel from which the data was calculated.
